@section detail {
  <b>Forerunner SDK:</b>
  <p>
    The Forerunner SDK contains all the support need to add the forerunner SDK to an existing Web Application. Forerunner 
    SDK package contains a readme.txt file. Read this file for addition information about this package. In order to enable
    Forerunner SDK remember to run the Set-FRConfig in the "Package Mamanger Console" window.
  </p>

  <p><i>Next Steps</i></p>
  <p>
    Once you have installed the SDK Package and run Set-FRConfig you will be ready to add one of the top level widgets to 
    your project. It is recommended you install the Getting Started package so you can use it as a running baseline as you 
    add Forerunner SDK support into your own application.

    You will need to have a page to put one of our top level widgets onto such as the Report Viewer EZ. In order to add the viewer,
    Explorer or Dashboard widgets you will need to make sure your page has the required script and style sheet references. The
    required references are as follows:
  </p>

